  "prompt": "Which phone should I buy under INR 15K?",
  "response": "As of my last update, several smartphones offer great value for money under INR 15,000. However, please verify the latest models and prices as they can change frequently. Here are a few popular options you might consider:\n\n1. **Xiaomi Redmi Note 11**:\n   - Display: 6.43-inch FHD+ AMOLED\n   - Processor: Snapdragon 680\n   - RAM: 4GB/6GB\n   - Storage: 64GB/128GB (expandable)\n   - Camera: 50MP main camera\n   - Battery: 5000mAh\n\n2. **Realme Narzo 50**:\n   - Display: 6.6-inch FHD+ IPS LCD\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G96\n   - RAM: 4GB/6GB\n   - Storage: 64GB/128GB (expandable)\n   - Camera: 50MP main camera\n   - Battery: 5000mAh\n\n3. **Samsung Galaxy F22**:\n   - Display: 6.4-inch FHD+ Super AMOLED\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G80\n   - RAM: 4GB/6GB\n   - Storage: 64GB/128GB (expandable)\n   - Camera: 48MP main camera\n   - Battery: 6000mAh\n\n4. **Poco M4 Pro**:\n   - Display: 6.43-inch FHD+ AMOLED\n   - Processor: MediaTek Dimensity 810\n   - RAM: 4GB/6GB\n   - Storage: 64GB/128GB (expandable)\n   - Camera: 64MP main camera\n   - Battery: 5000mAh\n\n5. **Vivo T1 5G**:\n   - Display: 6.58-inch FHD+ IPS LCD\n   - Processor: Snapdragon 695\n   - RAM: 4GB/6GB\n   - Storage: 128GB (expandable)\n   - Camera: 50MP main camera\n   - Battery: 5000mAh\n\nWhen choosing a smartphone, consider what features are most important to you, such as camera quality, battery life, performance, or software updates. It may also be beneficial to read recent reviews and check for any discounts or offers that retailers may have.",
